In[336]:
# Month mapping
month_mapping = {
    'Jan.': '01', 'Feb.': '02', 'Mar.': '03', 'Apr.': '04',
    'May.': '05', 'Jun.': '06', 'Jul.': '07', 'Aug.': '08',
    'Sep.': '09', 'Oct.': '10', 'Nov.': '11', 'Dec.': '12'
}

# Function to replace month names with numbers
def replace_month(date_str):
    for month_name, month_number in month_mapping.items():
        if month_name in date_str:
            return date_str.replace(month_name, month_number)
    return date_str

# Apply function to the 'date' column in the google DataFrame
google['date'] = google['date'].apply(replace_month)

In[476]:
model = Sequential()

model.add(Dense(units=64, activation='tanh', input_shape=(x_train.shape[1],)))
model.add(Dense(units=32, activation='relu'))
model.add(Dense(units=16, activation='relu'))

model.add(Dense(units=1))

model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='mean_squared_error')

history = model.fit(x_train, y_train, epochs=100, batch_size=32, validation_split=0.2, verbose=1)

y_pred = model.predict(x_test)

mse = mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred)
